# Terminology and architectural-framing migration for draft-ietf-schc-schclet-00
#
# Target vocabulary: draft-ietf-schc-architecture-06 (referred to below as [ARCH]).
# Assumes the two Trivial architecture clarifications in schc-architecture-edits.md
# are accepted, i.e. that [ARCH] states the single-SCHClet/single-Instance/single-
# Stratum relationship explicitly (Edit 1) and identifies "SCHC Stratum Header" with
# the Control Header (Edit 2).
#
# Migration rules applied:
#   - "SCHC Stratum Header" / "SCHC Header" / "SCHC Stratum functions" -> "Control Header"
#   - a SCHClet is framed as a subfunction hosted within a single Instance; a minimal
#     deployment is one SCHClet in one Instance on one Stratum (Instance selection
#     implicit, Discriminator/Control Header elided)
#   - interoperability is anchored on a compatible Context / Set of Rules, per [ARCH] 6.2
#   - "CoDA"/"CoDAs" -> "CDA"/"CDAs" (consistent with [ARCH] 3 and RFC 8724)
#   - no protocol behaviour, wire format, cardinality, or normative keyword is changed
#
# A new reference is required and assumed added to the References section:
#   [ARCH]  Pelov, A., Thubert, P., Minaburo, A., Lampin, Q., and M. Dumay,
#           "Static Context Header Compression (SCHC) Architecture",
#           draft-ietf-schc-architecture (Work in Progress).


