- include all aspects discussed in RFC8724, or other related SCHC RFCs.
- A SCHClet operates on a single Stratum and on a single SCHC Instance.
- Notions such as SCHC Stratum Header, SCHC Instance and Discriminator
- can therefore be omitted in the specification of a SCHClet.
+ A SCHClet is a self-contained function of SCHC, which may or may not
+ include all aspects discussed in RFC8724, or other related SCHC RFCs.
+ A SCHClet is hosted within a single SCHC Instance and operates on a
+ single Stratum.  When a deployment consists of a single such SCHClet,
+ Instance selection is implicit; notions such as the Control Header
+ [ARCH] and the Discriminator can therefore be omitted in the
+ specification of a SCHClet.

