## Section 2 (Terminology)

- *  SCHClet: A self-contained unit within the SCHC framework that
-    implements a specific SCHC function or a subset of SCHC
-    operations.  A SCHClet may implement aspects defined in RFC8724 or
-    other related SCHC RFCs, and MAY be combined with other SCHClets
-    or integrated into a full SCHC implementation.
+ *  SCHClet: A self-contained modular unit within the SCHC framework
+    that implements a specific SCHC function or a subset of SCHC
+    operations, corresponding to the SCHClet defined in [ARCH]
+    Section 4.2.2.3.  A SCHClet is hosted within a single SCHC Instance;
+    it may implement aspects defined in RFC8724 or other related SCHC
+    RFCs, and MAY be combined with other SCHClets within an Instance or
+    integrated into a full SCHC implementation.

- *  Full SCHC Implementation: An implementation that covers all
-    mandatory aspects of SCHC as defined in RFC8724, potentially
-    extended by additional functionalities introduced in subsequent/
-    related RFCs.
+ *  Full SCHC Implementation: An implementation that covers all
+    mandatory aspects of SCHC as defined in RFC8724, potentially
+    extended by additional functionalities introduced in subsequent/
+    related RFCs.  In [ARCH] terms, this is an Endpoint whose Instance
+    is configured with the full set of SCHC functions over a complete
+    Context.

- *  Full SCHC Implementation Configuration (Full Configuration): The
-    set of SCHC Profiles/configurations/parameters supported by a Full
-    SCHC Implementation.
+ *  Full SCHC Implementation Configuration (Full Configuration): The
+    set of SCHC Profiles/configurations/parameters supported by a Full
+    SCHC Implementation.  In [ARCH] terms, this corresponds to the
+    Instance Configuration together with the Context (Set of Rules) of
+    such an Instance.

- *  SCHClet Configuration: A subset of a Full Configuration, which are
-    implemented and supported by a given SCHClet.  This may be a
-    single SCHC Profile, or a set of such.
+ *  SCHClet Configuration: A subset of a Full Configuration that is
+    implemented and supported by a given SCHClet.  This may be a
+    single SCHC Profile, or a set of such.  In [ARCH] terms, it
+    corresponds to a constrained Instance Configuration together with a
+    compatible subset of the Context (Set of Rules); see [ARCH]
+    Section 6.2.


